\newpage \section*{Abstract}
Provinding safe water for dinking and cooking has ever been a problem for humanity. For many years, engineers has taken different path for all people to get water in there house. This is a everybody problem. Now, having water at home is not an issue; have safe water is different. The water tends to stagnate and facilitates, among others, the development of pathogenes. The population that inhales pathogens tends to be sick, especially of pneumonia in the case of Legionella pneumophila.

\paragraph{Bacteria details} Legionella pneumophila is a ubiquitous bacterium, which colonizes artificial environments, wet soils as well as natural fresh water\cite{jarraud2007legionellose}.

\paragraph{Bacteria transmission} Bacteria are transmitted to humans by aerosolization and less often by aspiration (to the lung) of colonized water. For now, relation between infection and water ingestion (to digestive organs) is not demonstrated.

